On 7 Nov 2016 2:07 am, "International Relations" <oir@iitm.ac.in wrote:

 Dear Students,


 The Intersection of Engineering and Business: A Masters Program in
 Technology Entrepreneurship

 Date Nov. 7th 

 Time: 5.30 p.m. to 6.30 p.m.

 Venue: Hall#1 IC &SR Building



 This talk is led by Sunny Shah
 ,
 Assistant Director & Faculty of ESTEEM Graduate Program
  at the University of Notre Dame. ESTEEM is the
 first multidisciplinary graduate program at Notre Dame, created in
 2009/2010 by the Colleges of Science, Engineering, and Business. ESTEEM is
 a oneyear graduate program in entrepreneurship and innovation targeted
 at STEM students and, now in its eighth academic year, is proving to be
 very successful on many fronts: attracting top students from national and
 international universities. excellent placement and a distinguishing
 capstone thesis component.



 The ESTEEM  program offers business skills with a
 focus on entrepreneurship and the commercialization of innovative research
 and technology. The students gain the knowledge, tools, and techniques
 required to take an idea all the way from concept to market through a
 capstone thesis where they work with University research or industry
 research to develop a comprehensive commercialization plan..



 Sunny Shah will talk about his PhD work in Biomedical Engineering and his
 pivot into a new career of technology commercialization and his current
 role in ESTEEM where he is incharge of the capstone thesis and
 the curriculum design. Additionally, he teaches a course in Business Model
 Canvas and Design Thinking.




 Regards

 Kavitha

